article.headline: Canisius 68, Navy 63
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Julius Coles scored 19 points and Frank Turner added 16 as Canisius beat Navy 68-63 on Saturday. Chris Gadley contributed 10 points and 11 rebounds for the Golden Griffins (4-7), who snapped a four-game losing streak. Kaleo Kina led Navy with 21 points, and Romeo Garcia chipped in with 11. The Midshipmen (8-3) have lost two of their last three following a seven-game winning streak. In a seesaw game that featured 15 lead changes, the Golden Griffins sealed the win with a 6-0 run over the final minute to seal the win. Gadley had three points during the stretch, converting a three-point play with 49 seconds left that gave Canisius a 65-63 lead. Navy missed five shots during the drought, including two straight by Kina. The Midshipmen conclude their five-game road trip at No. 18 Villanova on Monday.
